{"id":308286151,"question_id":2,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4 years, 12 months","timestamp":1583068226,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/308286151/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"41.3 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode(int x) { val = x; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        ListNode a = l1;\n        ListNode b = l2;\n        ListNode res = new ListNode(0);\n        ListNode temp = res;\n        int c = 0;\n        while( a != null || b != null )\n        {\n            int x = a != null ? a.val : 0 ;\n            int y = b != null ? b.val : 0;\n            int ans = x + y + c;\n            c = ans/10;\n            ListNode kk = new ListNode(ans%10);\n            //System.out.println(ans%10);\n            temp.next = kk;\n            temp = temp.next;\n            if ( a != null )\n            {\n                a = a.next;\n            }\n            if ( b != null )\n            {\n                b = b.next;\n            }\n        }\n        if ( c != 0 )\n        {\n            ListNode gg = new ListNode(c);\n            temp.next = gg;\n        }\n        return res.next;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
